I would note that I was going to complain about it only taking 24 years for Titan to get to Mars, but I did the math and it works out, so kudos on that.

I just don't see how we can conclude that there's an intelligent force at work here, though. An intelligence capable of exerting this much force on planetary bodies would have to be godlike or way up on the Kardashev scale.

On the Mars issue, I'm not even sure we would even be able to project that it could hit Mars, 200 years out, considering the sheer distances and the potentials for its trajectory to be affected by the gravitational pull of the Sun, or Jupiter, or any of the minor planets in the asteroid belt.







